cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper focuses on clustering search queries, which is a core problem in information retrieval. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper makes use of NLP techniques such as word2vec to obtain vector representations of queries. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a clustering algorithm to group queries based on their vector representations. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses machine learning and NLP techniques to understand user interests. 
5. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper deals with organizing and clustering large amounts of data (queries) which is a common problem in databases.
